text:
45 Lamberts Lane, north side, between Cooke Street and Richmond Avenue. The view is eastward from near Cooke Street.

May 19, 1935

P. L. Sperr

Richmond Avenue, at (left) and adjoining the S.E. corner of Benton Street. The house on the left is the Old Stone Tavern, named after Richmond Avenue's old name: Old Stone Road. The view is from Lamberts Lane.

May 19, 1935

P. L. Sperr

1382 Richmond Avenue, at the S.W. corner of Lamberts Lane, showing the Our Lady of Pity Roman Catholic Church (Italian). Note also the Traveling Library, operated by the Extension Division of the New York Public Library.

August 22, 1940

P. L. Sperr
